This paper is about sentiment analysis in Twitter, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as Linear SVM and Logistic Regressor, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses word embeddings, which are a popular technique in NLP and covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves feature engineering, which is covered in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper proposes an ensemble approach, which is a common technique in machine learning and covered in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
